word_mean_info__list.difference: 指因急躁或事务紧急而采取快速行动。
指以最快的速度向前奔驰。
着重指频率或速率运转加快。
指由于事的紧迫性或突然性而加速。
含义与hurry相近，但显得更仓促更慌乱。
指赶紧或匆忙地做某事或催促别人做某事，隐含草率或混乱意味。
普通用词，指增加速度、速率。

list.abstract: rush（英[rʌʃ]，美[rʌʃ]），英语单词，作动词为冲；奔；(使)仓促行事，作名词为冲；奔；突袭对方队员；工作样片。短语搭配有gold rush（淘金热）。例句为“Countries Rush for Upper Hand in Antarctica.（各国争相在南极占上风。）” 该单词为名词时的近义词为rapid，为及物动词时的近义词为sweep down，为不及物动词时的近义词为crash，反义词为linger、delay。
rush是一种松弛全身平滑肌的药物，诞生于美国，已经有超过30年的历史了，现在所谓的美版、英版是那时的剩余产品。至于加拿大版，加拿大从未生产过RUSH，其实还是美国的剩货，只是换了名和瓶贴，可以理解为专供中国市场的山寨货。

yingyinNormal.en: Lord Kaidu, there's no need to rush. Let him rush. Let him rush home to be king of his ger village. King of nomads and sheep.
yingyinNormal.zh: 海都大人，不要冲动。让他冲动，让他赶回去做他的蒙古包王，做牧民和羊群的王。

yingyinNormal.en: I appreciate your coming here in person. Especially during the, final rush.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我感谢你亲自过来，尤其在这最后冲刺阶段。

yingyinNormal.en: Maybe we shouldn't rush into having another kid?
yingyinNormal.zh: 也许我们不该急着领养孩子？

yingyinNormal.en: When will you tell him? There's no tearing rush.
yingyinNormal.zh: 您打算什么时候告诉他？这事不急。

yingyinNormal.en: That was such a rush! You've never stolen anything before?
yingyinNormal.zh: 刚才可真是太刺激了。你以前从没偷过什么东西吧？

yingyinNormal.en: Wait, wait, why does it say one-day rush? Since when do we offer a one-day rush?
yingyinNormal.zh: 等等，为什么他要一天内加急交货？我们什么时候提供加急服务了？

yingyinNormal.en: Joey. Why did we have to rush out of there so fast?
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们为什么要急着离开？

yingyinNormal.en: I don't want to rush him. Too much pressure and he will get traumatized.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我不想催促他，如果压力太大，他会受到精神创伤的。

yingyinNormal.en: Amazon offers one-day rush. Yeah, but they don't have to glue the books together.
yingyinNormal.zh: 亚马逊购书网提供加急服务的。但他们又不需要把书黏在一起。

yingyinNormal.en: Look, I'm sorry to rush this. You came up a little late, and there's a lot to do.
yingyinNormal.zh: 真抱歉，时间太紧了，你来的有点儿晚，有很多事要做。

yingyinNormal.en: Ooh, oh, I've gotta go. Whoa, oh, head rush. One more, and then I have to go. Cool.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我得走了，哇哦，脑充血，再一次，我必须得走了。酷。

yingyinNormal.en: Oh, of course. We rush around all morning. I haven't eaten breakfast and for nothing.
yingyinNormal.zh: 想都不用想。我们忙了一个早上，我连早餐都没吃，结果白费了。

yingyinNormal.en: I'm just not sure how smart it is to rush into a campaign with so little preparation.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我不确定现在几乎毫无准备就宣布参选是否有利。

yingyinNormal.en: And since she knows you're okay, I guess there's no real reason to rush. How about we walk?
yingyinNormal.zh: 我想她已经知道你安全了，没有理由那么着急了，我们去走走怎样？

yingyinNormal.en: Monica's right. We're talking about getting married here. Okay? She can't just rush into this.
yingyinNormal.zh: 莫妮卡说得对，这可是婚姻大事，她不能说嫁就嫁。

yingyinNormal.en: God, you are so strong. Or. I should rush through dinner with Joey and I can meet David at 9:00.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你意志太坚定了。或许我可以赶快跟乔伊吃完晚餐，然后九点跟大卫见面。

yingyinNormal.en: Well, it would be nice not to have to drive to Anaheim in rush hour. And don't ever call me Shelly.
yingyinNormal.zh: 能不用在高峰时段开去阿纳海姆也不错啊。再也不要叫我谢利。

yingyinNormal.en: Any progress? Yes. I will have the lobster ravioli. God Joey, this is taking forever. What's the rush? What?
yingyinNormal.zh: 可以点菜了吗？是的。我要点龙虾馄饨。天啊，乔伊，这得花一辈子的时间。干嘛这么急呢？ 噢。

yingyinNormal.en: Yes, I'm still holding. I need to place a rush t-shirt order. No, no, no, no, no. Don't put me on hold again.
yingyinNormal.zh: 是的，我一直在等呢，我需要下订单加急制作一批T恤，别别别，别再帮我转接客服部了。

yingyinNormal.en: Here, rush hour is just beginning. For many students in this desert community, buses are the only way to get to school.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这里的上下班高峰期才刚刚开始，对很多这片沙漠地区的学生来说，坐巴士是唯一去学校的办法。

examination_example.sentence: In fact, <highlight>rushing</highlight> to get your own ideas out there can cause colleagues to feel you don't value their opinions.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 事实上，急于表达自己的想法会让同事觉得你不重视他们的意见。

examination_example.sentence: So the TSA is now <highlight>rushing</highlight> to get new screeners on the line.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 因此，美国运输安全管理局正急于让新的安检人员上线。

examination_example.sentence: Overhead may be high and circulation lower, but <highlight>rushing</highlight> to eliminate its print edition would be a mistake, says BuzzFeed CEO Jonah Peretti.
examination_example.sentence_trans: BuzzFeed的首席执行官Jonah Peretti表示，运营费用可能会很高，发行量可能会降低，但匆忙取消印刷版将是一个错误。
